## ⚙️ How the App Works — Step by Step

### 1. 🚀 App Startup (`main.jsx`)

The app starts at `main.jsx`. It wraps everything in three **React Context Providers** and a **BrowserRouter**:

```
ToastProvider          ← global toast notifications
  └── CartProvider     ← global shopping cart state
        └── LoadingProvider  ← global loading screen state
              └── BrowserRouter
                    └── App
```

This means every component can access cart, toasts, and loading state from anywhere via hooks like `useCart()`, `useToast()`, `useLoading()`.

---

### 2. 🗺️ Routing (`App.jsx`)

`App.jsx` is the root layout. It controls:

| Route | What Shows |
|---|---|
| `/` | Redirects to `/home` |
| `/home` | HomePage (Hero + Products + Services + Contact) |
| `/services` | ServicesPage (Cinematic slider + Why Choose Us) |
| `/contact` | ContactPage (contact form) |

> **Lazy Loading**: `ServicesPage`, `ContactPage`, `Footer`, and `Bill` are loaded lazily with `React.lazy()` + `<Suspense>` to reduce initial bundle size.

**Two utility components inside App.jsx:**
- `ScrollToTop` — scrolls to top on every route change
- `RouteChangeLoader` — triggers the loading animation on route changes

---

### 3. 🧭 Navbar (`Navbar.jsx`)

- **Bilingual shop name**: Toggles between `NAMMA OORU` (English) and `நம்ம ஊரு` (Tamil) every 2 seconds
- **Scroll-aware**: Adds a shadow/background when you scroll past 10px
- **Cart badge**: Shows item count from `CartContext`
- **Mobile menu**: Hamburger menu for small screens

---

### 4. 🛍️ Products System

**Data** → `src/data/products.js`
All product data is hardcoded here as a JS array: `id`, `name`, `price`, `category`, `image`, `description`, `specs`, `gallery images`, etc.

**ProductsPage.jsx** reads this data and:
- Renders category filter buttons
- Shows a responsive grid of product cards
- Each card has an Add to Cart / quantity stepper button

**ProductDetailModal.jsx** opens when you click a product card:
- Shows full product details
- Image gallery (multiple images)
- Specs table
- Add to Cart button

---

### 5. 🛒 Cart System (`CartContext.jsx`)

The cart is global state managed via React Context. Functions:

| Function | What it does |
|---|---|
| `addToCart(product)` | Adds item or increments quantity |
| `removeFromCart(index)` | Removes item by index |
| `updateQuantity(index, qty)` | Sets quantity (removes if qty < 1) |
| `clearCart()` | Empties the cart |

**CartDrawer.jsx** is a slide-in sidebar that shows your cart items and a **Checkout** button.

---

### 6. 💰 Checkout & Invoice (`Bill.jsx`)

This is the most complex part. When you click **Checkout**:

1. Customer fills their name + phone
2. `handleCheckout()` in `App.jsx` sets `showBillPage = true` and shows `Bill.jsx`
3. `Bill.jsx` renders a **professional A4 invoice** with company logo, product table, totals, terms

**Auto-flow on mount (5 steps):**

```
900ms delay
    ↓
① Generate PDF (html2pdf.js) → auto-download to device
    ↓ 800ms
② Open WhatsApp for OWNER → full order details in a formatted message
    ↓ 3000ms gap
③ Open WhatsApp for CUSTOMER → order confirmation message
    ↓
All Done! 🎉
```

The invoice has:
- Invoice number (auto-generated: `INV-XXXXXX-XXX`)
- Customer details (Billed To section)
- Products table with quantity × price
- Amount in **words** (Indian numbering system: crores, lakhs)
- Terms & Conditions
- Signature section
- Company contact footer

**Download / Share:**
- `Download PDF` button re-triggers the PDF download
- `Share PDF` button uses the Web Share API (works on mobile) to share the PDF file

---

### 7. 📱 WhatsApp Integration

Two places WhatsApp is used:

1. **Invoice flow** (`Bill.jsx`): After checkout, auto-opens WhatsApp for both owner and customer
2. **Contact form** (`ContactForm.jsx`): Contact inquiries are sent via a WhatsApp pre-filled link
3. **WhatsAppFloat button** (`WhatsAppFloat.jsx`): Floating button in bottom-right always visible

---

### 8. 🎬 Loading Screen (`LoadingContext.jsx` + `LoadingScreen.jsx`)

- First page visit: Shows animated loading screen for **2 seconds** (stored in `sessionStorage` so it doesn't repeat in same session)
- Route changes: Shows a **fast 800ms** loading animation
- `triggerLoader(ms)` is called from anywhere via `useLoading()` hook

---

### 9. 🔔 Toast Notifications (`ToastContext.jsx`)

When items are added to cart (or other actions happen), a toast notification pops up using `addToast("message", "type")`.

---

### 10. 🧩 Services Page (`ServicesPage.jsx`)

- **Company Showcase** (lazy loaded): Cinematic scrolling image/video showcase of the company's services
- **Why Choose Us** section: 5 animated feature cards with counter animations (e.g., "1000+ Happy Customers" counts up when scrolled into view)

---

### 11. 📊 Google Sheets CRM (`sheets-demo/`)

A **completely separate mini-project** in the `sheets-demo/` folder — a plain HTML/CSS/JS frontend that connects to a **Google Apps Script Web App** to use Google Sheets as a simple database/CRM for customer, product, and invoice records.

> This is NOT connected to the main React app. It's a standalone experiment/demo.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **React 18** | UI framework |
| **Vite 7** | Build tool and dev server |
| **React Router DOM v7** | Client-side routing |
| **Tailwind CSS v3** | Utility-first styling |
| **Framer Motion** | Animations & transitions |
| **Lucide React** | Icons |
| **html2pdf.js** | PDF generation in browser |
| **canvas-confetti** | (Available, for celebrations) |
| **firebase** | (Available, for future use) |
| **gh-pages** | Deploy to GitHub Pages |
| **Terser** | JS minification in production build |
| **vite-plugin-image-optimizer** | Auto-compress images on build |

---

## 🌐 Deployment

- **Dev server**: `npm run dev` → runs at `http://localhost:5173`
- **Build**: `npm run build` → outputs to `dist/` folder
- **Deploy**: `npm run deploy` → builds then pushes `dist/` to GitHub Pages
- **Live URL**: `https://jiteshgoodboy0109-jit.github.io/namma-ooru-smart-Gliffy.X-`

---

## 🔄 Data Flow Summary

```
User visits website
    ↓
LoadingScreen shown (first visit only)
    ↓
Navbar + Hero displayed
    ↓
User browses Products (data from products.js)
    ↓
Clicks product → ProductDetailModal opens
    ↓
Clicks "Add to Cart" → CartContext updates
    ↓
Cart badge in Navbar updates
    ↓
User opens CartDrawer → sees items
    ↓
Clicks Checkout → enters Name + Phone
    ↓
Bill.jsx renders →
    Auto PDF download
    → WhatsApp opens for Owner (order details)
    → WhatsApp opens for Customer (confirmation)
    ↓
User clicks "Go Home" → Cart cleared, back to /home
```
